The second star is just for effort... They're clearly trying hard to act like this is a restaurant, but it's a bar. The waitress got every single order wrong, seemed very confused by basic requests, and the manager/owner was lecturing her and making her more flustered right in front of us. The food was not well prepared-- just thrown together, and came out to the table all in different pieces. We were one of three total tables the whole time we were there, so I have no idea what the service would have been like if the place was full! Lots of work to do on this place before I would eat here again.

The food is fine, and the delivery used to be great, but Borough really needs to be removed from Seamless. Half of our recent orders have turned up VERY late, and we have had to call the restaurant to find out what's going on by the time the food finally arrives. The excuse when we call is always that they are "backed up." Tonight, it took over 135 minutes to deliver our order, and when we called after 90 minutes of not hearing anything from them, the food had not even been made yet. Again, no phone call from the restaurant, and when we called them, they blamed Seamless for continuing to send them orders after they got backed up. Every other restaurant that we've used on Seamless that's run late has called us to let us know and give us the choice of canceling.
